      %h2 About Boston Sleep Reading Center
      %br
      %h4
        We strive to provide you the best service for reading physiological data.
        With a dedicated team of polysomnologists and a history of scoring over
        50,000 sleep studies, you will receive scored data that will be used by
        fellow researchers in the years to come.
      %br
      %p
        The Boston Sleep Reading Center (BSRC), housed in the Division of Sleep and Circadian Disorders at Brigham and Women’s Hospital in Boston, Massachusetts, provides high-quality and reliable analysis of physiological data to support industry funded and observational studies, equipment validation projects, pharmacological studies, comparative effectiveness research and clinical trials. Areas of expertise include polysomnography, actigraphy, oximetry, quantitative EEG analysis and more. The SRC provides comprehensive equipment certification services, protocol development and standardization, quality control monitoring, and staff training and certification services. The SRC also contains a Statistical Core that can provide statistical analysis support and an Informatics and Data Management Core that develops highly interactive tools capable of supporting multicenter studies, clinical trials and data repositories. The program includes a staff of approximately 30 individuals, including epidemiologists, biostatisticians, informaticians, clinicians, data managers, research assistants and study coordinators.
      %br
      = link_to 'Get in Touch', '#contact', class: 'btn btn-default btn-lg', data: { object: 'scroll-anchor' }
      %br
      %br
